### Bin Packing Background:
The bin packing problem is a classic optimization problem where you have a set of items of various sizes and a set of bins of fixed capacity. The goal is to pack all items into the fewest number of bins possible without exceeding the bin capacity. In this case, the bins have varying capacities, and the item is to be placed into the bin that gives the highest priority score.

